  "prompt": "What is the salary of a cosmologist?",
  "response": "The salary of a cosmologist can vary widely depending on factors such as:\n\n1. Education level (Ph.D. is typically required)\n2. Experience\n3. Employer (university, research institution, government agency)\n4. Location\n5. Specific role (research scientist, professor, etc.)\n\nGenerally, cosmologists can expect:\n- Entry-level: $50,000 - $70,000 per year\n- Mid-career: $70,000 - $120,000 per year\n- Experienced/senior positions: $120,000 - $180,000+ per year\n\nAcademic positions like university professors might have salaries in a similar range, while those working for NASA or other research agencies might have slightly different compensation structures.\n\nThese are approximate ranges and can fluctuate based on individual circumstances and current job market conditions.",
